cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.MA, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper studies the SIRS spreading process over complex networks, which is a topic closely related to social and information networks. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the stability and eradication of epidemics, which can be viewed as a control problem. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper uses Markov chain models to study the SIRS epidemics, which involves analyzing the mixing time of the Markov chain, a topic related to data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper studies the behavior of a system of agents (nodes in a network) under the influence of an epidemic, which can be viewed as a multiagent system. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper uses mathematical models to study the SIRS epidemics, which can be viewed as a topic related to neural and evolutionary computing.
